				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4518036#post-4558772</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-4518036/the-last-man#post-4558772</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 22 Mar 2020 01:15:18 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>lRaziel1</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2034342</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I didn't really understand it fully either, but my take is that all that thing wanted was to retrieve SCP-001 &quot;The broken god&quot; (haven't read it yet, way too long) but as people kept attacking it, it obliterated the world back, and turns out that maybe the way we had been stopping that thing's communications with it's &quot;mothership&quot;, which was by jamming and also decoding their communications with a satellite barrier, was also the way to stop them. Simply intercept their communication system and tell it that what they wanted went to shit and that they need to abort the mission. So the world literally ending was completely unnecessary.</p> <p>Take this with a grain of salt though.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
